have the wood on
Homonym Number:
Word Class: phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:to have the/an advantage over, to have the upper hand of: possibly f. tree-falling or axemen's contests, where one wins because one is a chip or thickness of wood ahead of an opponent who loses because he still has a piece of wood to sever before his trunk or block falls: but cf. ADD, and <i>have the googs on</i>




Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
